(AP Photo/Alex Brandon)WASHINGTON (AP) — President Donald Trump claimed the “total” authority Monday to decide how and when to reopen the economy after weeks of tough social distancing guidelines aimed at fighting the new coronavirus.
“When somebody is president of the United States, the authority is total,” Trump said at the White House.
And he has refused to publicly pressure states to enact stay-at-home restrictions, citing his belief in local control of government.